            <score>7.0</score>
            <value>CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:H/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H</value>
          </severity>
        </severities>
        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:H/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H|summary=OpenSSH is prone to a privilege scalation vulnerability in
  certain configurations.|insight=sshd failed to correctly initialise supplemental groups when
  executing an AuthorizedKeysCommand or AuthorizedPrincipalsCommand, where a
  AuthorizedKeysCommandUser or AuthorizedPrincipalsCommandUser directive has been set to run the
  command as a different user. Instead these commands would inherit the groups that sshd was started
  with.

  Depending on system configuration, inherited groups may allow
  AuthorizedKeysCommand/AuthorizedPrincipalsCommand helper programs to gain unintended privilege.

  Neither AuthorizedKeysCommand nor AuthorizedPrincipalsCommand are enabled by default in
  sshd_config.|affected=OpenSSH versions 6.2 through 8.7.|impact=|solution=Update to version 8.8 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 8.8 or later.</solution>
